sql:
SELECT AVG(frame_delay) AS average_frame_delay
FROM telemetry_data
WHERE mission_id = 1;

SELECT uav_id, uav_name, model, deployment_status
FROM uavs
ORDER BY uav_name ASC;

SELECT mission_id, mission_name, start_time
FROM missions
ORDER BY start_time DESC;

SELECT mission_name
FROM missions
ORDER BY mission_name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- Quality of Service (QoS) in the context of telemetry data typically refers to the service quality or priority assigned to the data transmission; 
- Average data received and sent are measured in kilobytes (KB); 
- Average process times, message creation delays, frame delays, and offset received are measured in milliseconds (ms).
